The paper deals with formalism and decidability of cellular automata, which are typically studied in computer science and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses stochastic processes and correlations, which are relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and systems and control theory (cs.SY). The paper's focus on simulations and intrinsic simulation relations suggests that it may also be relevant to computational complexity (cs.CC) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
